===Etymology 1===
{{root|en|ine-pro|*bʰereg-|*bʰerHǵ-}}
The {{glossary|adjective}} is derived from {{inh|en|enm|bright|t=giving off much light; of colour or light: brilliant, intense; brightly lit; gleaming, shining; glorious, resplendent; of a person: beautiful, fair, rosy; wonderful; clear; of eyesight: keen; (''figuratively'') free from sin; enlightened}}{{nb...|beorht, brigh, brighte, brigth, brihgte, briht, brist, briȝht, briȝte, briȝtt, brit, brith, britȝ, briȝt, bryght, bryghte, brygth, bryhit, bryht, bryhte, bryth, brytȝ, bryȝt, bryȝth, bryȝthe, (Early Middle English) breht, breyt, bricch, brich, bricht, brict, brigst, brigt, brih, brihet, brihht, brist, britht, briycte, brytd, bryþt|otherforms=1}},<ref>{{R:MED Online|pos=adj|id=MED6031}}</ref> from {{inh|en|ang|bryht}}, a {{glossary|metathetic}} variant of {{m|ang|byrht}} {{qualifier|Anglian}}, {{m|ang|breht}} {{qualifier|Northumbrian}}, {{m|ang|beorht}} {{qualifier|West Saxon}}, {{m|ang|berht|t=bright, clear}}{{nb...|(Late Old English) beorct, (Old English) biorht, breoht, (rare) beort, beoruht|otherforms=1}} from {{inh|en|gmw-pro|*berht}},<ref>Compare {{R:OED Online|pos=adj.'' and ''n|id=23303|date=March 2021|nodot=1}}; {{R:Lexico|pos=adj.'' and ''n}}</ref> from {{inh|en|gem-pro|*berhtaz|t=bright, shining}}, ultimately from {{der|en|ine-pro|*bʰereg-|t=to gleam, whiten}}, {{m|ine-pro|*bʰerHǵ-|t=to shine}}.

The {{glossary|noun}} is derived from {{inh|en|enm|bright|t=brightness, brilliance; daylight; light}}, from {{m|enm|bright|pos=adjective}}:<ref>{{R:MED Online|pos=n|id=MED6030}}</ref> see above.

The English word is cognate with {{cog|sq|bardhë|t=white}}, {{cog|nl|brecht}} {{qualifier|in personal names}}, {{cog|is|bjartur|t=bright}}, {{cog|lt|brekšta|t=to dawn}}, {{cog|mga|brafad|t=blink of an eye}}, {{cog|no|bjart|t=bright, clear, shining}}, {{cog|fa|برازیدن|tr=barâzidan|t=to beautify; to befit}}, {{cog|ru|бре́зжить|t=to dawn; to flicker faintly, glimmer; (''figuratively'') of a hope, thought, etc.: to begin to manifest, emerge}}, {{cog|sa|भ्राजते}}, {{cog|sco|bricht|t=bright}}, {{cog|cy|berth|t=beautiful, fair, fine}} {{qualifier|obsolete}}.

